  https://github.com/headroomlabs-ai/headroom
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

The port is a MODIFIED derivative: it is written from scratch in Node.js (Headroom's
live implementation is Rust), diverges deliberately from upstream (it spills dropped
array rows to a file referenced as `full=<path>` instead of Headroom's content-addressed
`<<ccr:HASH …>>` handle, and it uses a distinct-count uniqueness budget in place of
Headroom's SimHash + Kneedle `compute_optimal_k`), and adds fnd-specific pipeline stages
(ADF→markdown, noise drop, long-string truncation) that are not part of SmartCrusher.

The fixtures under tests/parity/fixtures/smart_crusher/ are copied verbatim from the
Headroom repository (tests/parity/fixtures/smart_crusher/, same Apache-2.0 license). They
are the porting contract: tests/json-slim-fixtures.mjs runs the port against them and
pins byte-parity (16/17) or, where JavaScript number semantics prevent it, value-parity
(1/17 — the time_series fixture, whose float-valued whole numbers `0.0` re-serialize to
`0`).

log-slim.cjs — log-compressor port attribution
==============================================

plugins/fnd/scripts/log-slim.cjs contains a JavaScript re-implementation of Headroom's
LogCompressor and the log branch of its regex ContentDetector.

  Headroom
  Copyright 2025 Headroom Contributors
  https://github.com/headroomlabs-ai/headroom
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

The port is a MODIFIED derivative: it is written from scratch in Node.js (Headroom's live
implementation is Rust), ported from the Python shim
(headroom/transforms/log_compressor.py — whose scoring/parse regexes and constants the
port follows closely) with the two Rust-only passes (flavor-aware stack-trace termination and
runtime-frame collapse) taken from crates/headroom-core/src/transforms/log_compressor.rs,
and it diverges deliberately from upstream: it does NOT emit Headroom's CCR/MD5 spill marker
at runtime (json-slim and the mcp-slim hook spill the whole original as the recovery net; the
marker is reproduced only under `ccrStore:true`), it annotates deduped warnings with ` ×N`
(upstream drops duplicates silently), its omitted-lines trailer reports per-level counts of
lines ACTUALLY omitted rather than the log's total level composition, and the log-branch
CONTENT DETECTOR gates on structural log-level FIELDS (uppercase/first, bracketed, or `:`/`[`
delimited) instead of a case-insensitive keyword-anywhere scan, so prose/markdown/docs that
merely mention error words pass through untouched. The Drain-style LogTemplate reformat, the
magika ML detector, and aho-corasick are explicitly NOT ported (a plain substring / regex
scan is sufficient at our sizes).

The 20 fixtures under tests/parity/fixtures/log_compressor/ are copied verbatim from the Headroom
repository (tests/parity/fixtures/log_compressor/, same Apache-2.0 license) — genuine recordings of
Headroom's own LogCompressor, exactly as tests/parity/fixtures/smart_crusher/ are for SmartCrusher.
They are the porting CONTRACT: tests/json-slim-fixtures.mjs runs the port against them and pins it
BYTE-EXACT to upstream's recorded output — 19/20 fully identical (body, format_detected, cache_key,
compressed_line_count, stats, compression_ratio), and 1/20 (the sole 305-line compressing fixture)
byte-identical on every line EXCEPT the omitted-lines trailer, which is exempted for exactly one
enumerated deviation and asserted against our own semantics. Each fixture's integrity is checked by
recomputing the recorder's canonical digest: upstream's field is named `input_sha256` but stores
sha256 of the canonical payload `{transform, input, config, fn}` (recorder.py `_canonical_digest`,
the filename being its first 16 hex chars), NOT sha256 of the input string — so the harness pins that
canonical digest against both the stored field and the filename to detect any tampering.

The three enumerated deviations, and where each is asserted:
  1. Omitted-lines trailer. Upstream reports per-level TOTALS (`[297 lines omitted: 1 ERROR, 300
     INFO]`, listing a KEPT error and a breakdown that exceeds the omitted count); the port reports
     lines ACTUALLY omitted (`[297 lines omitted: 297 INFO]`) — the honesty fix from adversarial
     review. This is the ONLY line exempted on the one compressing fixture; the test re-derives our
     trailer from upstream's own body+stats and pins it, byte-compares every other line, and
     recomputes compression_ratio for our (shorter) output.
  2. Warning-dedupe ` ×N` annotation. Upstream drops duplicate warnings silently; the port annotates
     the survivor ` ×N`. No upstream fixture reaches this path (the compressing fixture has zero
     warnings), so it is covered by the dedupe unit tests, not the fixtures.
  3. Runtime CCR-marker omission. Upstream always emits the `[N lines compressed to M. Retrieve more:
     hash=…]` MD5 marker; the port emits it only under `ccrStore:true` (json-slim/mcp-slim spill the
     whole original as the recovery net at runtime). The fixtures run with `ccrStore:true`, so the
     marker is reproduced and pinned byte-for-byte; the runtime omits it.

